<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1282 </DOCNO><TEXT>Recent approaches to solve the solar neutrino problem comprise both newtheoretical ideas and newly developed techniques for huge undergrounddetectors. The investigation of electrons produced by neutrinos fromthe /sup 8/B decay is particularly interesting. Earlier bubble chamberphotographs of electron tracks (5-20 MeV) in two liquids, the measurementsof their energy and direction, may help to optimize the design of thesedetectors.</TEXT></DOC>